.el .ds Aq '
.TH g-config 1  "g-config " 
.SH NAME
g\-config \- Open interactive config editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBg\-config\fR [\fB\-\-edit\fR] [\fB\-\-path\fR] [\fB\-\-themes\fR] [\fB\-\-list\fR] [\fB\-\-menu\fR] [\fB\-\-get\fR] [\fB\-\-new\-theme\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIKEY\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Open interactive config editor
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-edit\fR
Open config file in $EDITOR
.TP
\fB\-\-path\fR
Print the path to the config file
.TP
\fB\-\-themes\fR
List available themes (built\-in + custom) and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fR
Print every editable scalar setting with its current value and help text
.TP
\fB\-\-menu\fR
Interactive menu: pick a setting, see its current value, choose a new one
.TP
\fB\-\-get\fR \fI<KEY>\fR
Print the exact current value of `<key>` (scripting\-friendly). Pair with a key positional: `g config \-\-get ui.log_limit`
.TP
\fB\-\-new\-theme\fR
Launch the interactive theme creator.  Writes a new TOML file under `~/.config/g/themes/<name>.toml` that extends an existing theme and overrides only the colors you choose
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIKEY\fR]
Optional positional key — when present alone, fuzzy\-search the summary for matching lines (legacy behaviour)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
g\-config\-set(1)
Set a config key, validated against the editable schema
.TP
g\-config\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
